data.title: Euro 2020 Rosters: Who Made the Cut?
data.meta_description: Spain left Sergio Ramos off its roster because of fitness concerns, Germany restored a pair of veterans and France selected Karim Benzema.
data.text:
Liverpool’s Trent Alexander-Arnold was one of four right backs included in England’s final 26-man roster for this summer’s European Championship as Manager Gareth Southgate trimmed his roster hours before the tournament deadline.

But after one exhibition game, he was out again.

Alexander-Arnold, a late inclusion in England’s team, withdrew on Thursday, a day after sustaining a thigh injury in a friendly match against Austria. England and Liverpool confirmed that the young defender was out.

“A scan on Thursday confirmed the 22-year-old will be unable to play in the forthcoming tournament so he’s withdrawn from the England squad to return to his club for rehabilitation,” England said in a statement posted on Twitter.
